tie Kirk Brodows and Ronald Goga for.

10th on Pitt’s all—time list.

Backing up Gaul will be redshirt
sophomore Joe Conlan, who recorded 22
shutouts inhis last two seasons at Strath
Haven High School. .

The Panthers open the season at
Bucknell on Friday, and the home opener
is Sept. .13 against Duquesne at Shaler.

Pitt has only made two appearances in
the Big East postseason tournament in 15
years, the last coming in 1995, when the
Panthers reached the ﬁnal before losing to
St. John’s. ’

